# WHAT IT IS
#   playwright-slack-report is the de-facto Playwright →
#   Slack notification reporter.  Invoked either as a Playwright
#   custom reporter inside `playwright.config.ts` or as a
#   standalone CLI consuming a Playwright JSON results file,
#   it parses the test summary (`passed`, `failed`, `skipped`,
#   `flaky`, `aborted`, per-spec breakdowns, retry attempts,
#   stderr / stdout / attachments), and pushes a typed Slack
#   message to one or more channels via a bot (Web API) or to
#   an incoming-webhook URL — controllable per-invocation via
#   the JSON config file's `sendUsingBot` / `sendUsingWebhook`
#   blocks.  The bot path constructs a `@slack/web-api`
#   `WebClient(process.env.SLACK_BOT_USER_OAUTH_TOKEN,
#   {logLevel, agent})` and posts a Block Kit summary; the
#   webhook path constructs `new IncomingWebhook(url, {agent})`
#   from `@slack/webhook` and posts the same.  Failures can be
#   threaded onto the parent message
#   (`config.showInThread = true`) and an arbitrary custom
#   block-builder function can be loaded via
#   `config.customLayout.source` + `functionName` (or its async
#   sibling `config.customLayoutAsync.*`).  Meta entries support
#   `__ENV_<NAME>` placeholders so CI can stamp the build URL,
#   commit hash, branch, or env-name onto every notification.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cli.ts commander.js chain
#                       at the repo root; extracted via `gh api
#                       repos/ryanrosello-og/playwright-slack-
#                       report/contents/cli.ts`)
#
#   playwright-slack-report - cli [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -c, --config <PATH>            Configuration file for the
#                                    CLI app  (e.g.
#                                    ./config.json) — the JSON
#                                    schema is enforced by
#                                    src/cli/cli_schema.ts
#                                    (ICliConfig: sendResults,
#                                     sendUsingBot {channels,
#                                                   showInThread,
#                                                   sendCustom
#                                                   BlocksInThread
#                                                   AfterIndex},
#                                     sendUsingWebhook {webhook
#                                                       Url},
#                                     proxy, slackLogLevel,
#                                     maxNumberOfFailures,
#                                     disableUnfurl, meta {key,
#                                                          value},
#                                     customLayout {source,
#                                                   functionName},
#                                     customLayoutAsync {source,
#                                                        function
#                                                        Name})
#
#     -j, --json-results <PATH>      Generated Playwright JSON
#                                    results file  (e.g.
#                                    ./results.json — pass the
#                                    output of Playwright's
#                                    built-in `json` reporter)
#
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -V, --version                  Show version  (1.0.0 CLI
#                                    surface; package version
#                                    1.1.110)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `@slack/web-api ^7.15.1` AND
#   `@slack/webhook ^7.0.8` declared in package.json — both are
#   the canonical Node Slack SDK packages, maintained by
#   slackapi at slackapi/node-slack-sdk (15,000+ stars; the
#   official Slack Node.js client suite that the entire Bolt
#   for JavaScript framework is built on top of).
#
#   `@slack/web-api` exposes the typed `WebClient(token,
#   {logLevel, agent, retryConfig, slackApiUrl})` constructor,
#   every typed `client.chat.postMessage({channel, text, blocks,
#   attachments, thread_ts, reply_broadcast, unfurl_links,
#   unfurl_media, link_names, parse, mrkdwn, icon_emoji,
#   icon_url, username, as_user, metadata})` /
#   `client.chat.update` / `client.chat.delete` /
#   `client.chat.postEphemeral` / `client.chat.scheduleMessage` /
#   `client.chat.deleteScheduledMessage` / `client.conversations.
#   list` / `client.conversations.history` / `client.conversa
#   tions.replies` / `client.conversations.members` / `client.
#   conversations.info` / `client.conversations.open` /
#   `client.users.info` / `client.users.list` / `client.users.
#   lookupByEmail` / `client.users.profile.get` / `client.users.
#   profile.set` / `client.files.upload` / `client.files.upload
#   V2` / `client.files.info` / `client.files.list` / `client.
#   files.delete` / `client.views.publish` / `client.views.open`
#   / `client.views.update` / `client.views.push` / `client.
#   reactions.add` / `client.reactions.remove` / `client.
#   reactions.get` / `client.reactions.list` / `client.search.
#   messages` / `client.search.files` / `client.search.all`
#   request + response model, the typed
#   `WebAPICallResult` / `LogLevel` (`DEBUG | INFO | WARN |
#   ERROR`) / `RetryOptions` /
#   `Block` / `KnownBlock` (`SectionBlock`, `HeaderBlock`,
#   `DividerBlock`, `ImageBlock`, `ActionsBlock`, `ContextBlock`,
#   `FileBlock`, `InputBlock`, `RichTextBlock`,
#   `VideoBlock`) primitives, the `MessageAttachment` schema,
#   every `KnownBlockElement` variant
#   (`Button`, `ChannelsSelect`, `Checkboxes`, `ConversationsSelect`,
#   `Datepicker`, `Datetimepicker`, `EmailInput`, `ExternalSelect`,
#   `FileInput`, `Image`, `MultiChannelsSelect`, `MultiConversations
#   Select`, `MultiExternalSelect`, `MultiStaticSelect`, `MultiUsers
#   Select`, `NumberInput`, `Overflow`, `PlainTextInput`,
#   `RadioButtons`, `RichTextInput`, `RichTextSection`, `RichText
#   List`, `RichTextQuote`, `RichTextPreformatted`, `StaticSelect`,
#   `Timepicker`, `URLInput`, `UsersSelect`,
#   `WorkflowButton`), `KnownTextElement` (`PlainTextObject`,
#   `MrkdwnTextObject`), built-in pagination helpers, automatic
#   rate-limit + retry handling, and the proxy-agent escape
#   hatch via `agent`.
#
#   `@slack/webhook` exposes the parallel `IncomingWebhook(url,
#   {agent, defaults})` constructor with `webhook.send(message)`
#   and the typed `IncomingWebhookSendArguments` payload
#   (`text`, `blocks`, `attachments`, `link_names`,
#   `unfurl_links`, `unfurl_media`, `username`, `icon_emoji`,
#   `icon_url`, `channel`).
#
#   playwright-slack-report's `cli.ts` constructs both clients
#   on demand: `new WebClient(process.env.SLACK_BOT_USER_OAUTH_
#   TOKEN, {logLevel: config.slackLogLevel, agent})` for the bot
#   path, `new IncomingWebhook(config.sendUsingWebhook.webhook
#   Url, {agent})` for the webhook path, and routes typed Block
#   Kit payloads (built by `src/SlackClient.ts` and `src/Slack
#   WebhookClient.ts` via `slack-block-builder`-style fluent
#   chains) to the corresponding API.  Verified via:
